HEADWORD: Memnon
<hw>Mem"non</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from Gr. <?/,
lit., the Steadfast, Resolute, the son of <persfn>Tithonus</persfn> and
<persfn>Aurora</persfn>, and king of the Ethiopians, killed by
<persfn>Achilles</persfn>.]</ety> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>A celebrated
Egyptian statue near Thebes, said to have the property of emitting a
harplike sound at sunrise.</def>⟦br⟧
